    <note>Han(1) Zhongtong [643] His sister's husband, Lu(9) Wenzhong [3659], has the same generational name as Lu(9) Haowen's [8099] sons and nephews. His mother, Liu(2) Shi, was buried in Huzhou, Wucheng xian, which we assume was Zhongtong's address. His father, Hu(2) [17942], has the same generational name as the great grandsons of Yi(2) [8049], and both chronological logic, the fact that Hu(2) and Zhongtong followed civil service careers with no indication of any South China ancestors holding degrees, and probable intermarriage with the Dongping Lu, all make it highly probable that Hu(2) and Zhongtong were Nanyang Han that moved to Huzhou. XNYL, 172.20a, 173.13b, 18a, 174.3a, 10b; XZZTJ, 138.19a; Sun  Di, Daquanji, 64.11b. CBD, 5, 4166.</note>
